commit_message:
Unpin beaker-rspec

The latest version of beaker tries to manage sshd_config[1] in order to
pass through environment variables. JJB also tries to manage
sshd_config by adding Match blocks to securely allow root SSH[2]. When
beaker tries to append the PermitUserEnvironment line after the Match
blocks, SSH fails to open port 22 and beaker can't SSH in to the
node[3]. This patch unpins beaker-rspec and adds set_env: false to the
nodepool nodesets so that the set_env method is never called and does
not try to mess with the sshd_config.

[1] https://github.com/puppetlabs/beaker/blob/master/lib/beaker/host_prebuilt_steps.rb#L528
[2] http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack-infra/project-config/tree/jenkins/jobs/puppet-module-jobs.yaml#n42
[3] http://logs.openstack.org/61/185161/1/check/gate-puppet-nova-puppet-beaker-rspec-dsvm-centos7/cd81608/console.html.gz#_2015-05-22_22_05_46_933
[4] https://github.com/puppetlabs/beaker/blob/master/lib/beaker/host_prebuilt_steps.rb#L502

Change-Id: If23c1e8c5f89e0b9c36ea0aaa3aea047a371bd73

commit_message:
Unpin beaker-rspec

The latest version of beaker tries to manage sshd_config[1] in order to
pass through environment variables. JJB also tries to manage
sshd_config by adding Match blocks to securely allow root SSH[2]. When
beaker tries to append the PermitUserEnvironment line after the Match
blocks, SSH fails to open port 22 and beaker can't SSH in to the
node[3]. This patch unpins beaker-rspec and adds set_env: false to the
nodepool nodesets so that the set_env method is never called and does
not try to mess with the sshd_config.

[1] https://github.com/puppetlabs/beaker/blob/master/lib/beaker/host_prebuilt_steps.rb#L528
[2] http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack-infra/project-config/tree/jenkins/jobs/puppet-module-jobs.yaml#n42
[3] http://logs.openstack.org/61/185161/1/check/gate-puppet-nova-puppet-beaker-rspec-dsvm-centos7/cd81608/console.html.gz#_2015-05-22_22_05_46_933
[4] https://github.com/puppetlabs/beaker/blob/master/lib/beaker/host_prebuilt_steps.rb#L502

Change-Id: Ifc711e9d0338d3f524f4a6f751a95a9868e15078

commit_message:
Extract logging config into a helper function

It's an error to have a library class set up logging output for you, as
this will prevent a consumer from doing what they need to do with their
logging config.

However, for simple scripts, the complexity of what needs to be done for
"normal" operation is a bit onerous.

Create a simple helper function that a user can run to set up the two
most common types of logging expected for simple scripts.

Change-Id: I81ef597712ff885d95194c6e29a45a1b2e7f86b9

commit_message:
Give client plugins the chance to not register

This change improves the client plugin registration process by giving
each plugin a is_available() class method that can prevent the plugin's
registration when there are missing dependencies.

Change-Id: Ief965d033f02f795d5be9beccae5e4b0b96d10b1
Closes-Bug: #1462555

I think this is a good idea and matches what we try to do with libvirt.'}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2015-05-15 21:31:03.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

This fails startup if you're not running 5.1.0.

The commit message says the minimum version tested is 5.1.0 (is that in the nsx ci?).  Saying versions below 5.1.0 are not tested is different than outright failing to start nova-compute if that's what someone is running with.

I think this would at least but a DocImpact/UpgradeImpact for Liberty release notes - and if you want to enforce a minimum 5.1.0 version then I think that has to wait for the M release and you could log a warning in Liberty that < 5.1.0 is deprecated, that's what I did for libvirt:

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/183220/

Also, is there anything like the libvirt distro support matrix anywhere for vcenter and the nova driver?"}, {'account_id': 4393, 'date': '2015-05-15 21:39:32.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: -Code-Review

So docimpact, yeah. I still think it's fine to exit, and I don't think we need to drag this out for a deprecation cycle."}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2015-05-15 21:39:43.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

So I think this would require a deprecation warning cycle for liberty and then enforce 5.1.0 in M, and get the docs updated to say that only 5.1.0 is supported in M.'}, {'account_id': 1653, 'date': '2015-05-15 22:08:20.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 964, 'date': '2015-05-15 22:09:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

commit_message:
VMware: enforce minimum support VC version

Provide a check that validates the minimum supported VC version for
the VMware driver. The minimum version tested is 5.1.0.

In L we will log a warning. From M this will be enforced.

DocImpact

Change-Id: If1a0767d19c26f5e028d1f8f57ede9716e19303f

The latest version of beaker tries to manage sshd_config[1] in order to
pass through environment variables. JJB also tries to manage
sshd_config by adding Match blocks to securely allow root SSH[2]. When
beaker tries to append the PermitUserEnvironment line after the Match
blocks, SSH fails to open port 22 and beaker can't SSH in to the
node[3]. This patch unpins beaker-rspec and adds set_env: false to the

commit_message:
Unpin beaker-rspec

The latest version of beaker tries to manage sshd_config[1] in order to
pass through environment variables. JJB also tries to manage
sshd_config by adding Match blocks to securely allow root SSH[2]. When
beaker tries to append the PermitUserEnvironment line after the Match
blocks, SSH fails to open port 22 and beaker can't SSH in to the
node[3]. This patch unpins beaker-rspec and adds set_env: false to the
nodepool nodesets so that the set_env method is never called and does
not try to mess with the sshd_config.

[1] https://github.com/puppetlabs/beaker/blob/master/lib/beaker/host_prebuilt_steps.rb#L528
[2] http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack-infra/project-config/tree/jenkins/jobs/puppet-module-jobs.yaml#n42
[3] http://logs.openstack.org/61/185161/1/check/gate-puppet-nova-puppet-beaker-rspec-dsvm-centos7/cd81608/console.html.gz#_2015-05-22_22_05_46_933
[4] https://github.com/puppetlabs/beaker/blob/master/lib/beaker/host_prebuilt_steps.rb#L502

Change-Id: I867012fd6296aff407683250a2f65334a6be0e99

commit_message:
Add libuuid devel packages

python-qpid-proton does something similar to pyzmq when libzmq is not
installed. It bundles the underlying library and builds it.
Unfortunately, python-qpid-proton currently has a dependency on
`libuuid` and therefore, it depends on the devel packages to be present.

This dependency will be removed in the future but it'll take time. Until
that happens, I'm adding uuid-dev to the list of packages to install by
default.

See related system-config change: Iae4d7138311eec0cd90c0865f30b84a98ce3c142

Change-Id: I65f24262c2470c6d75b5b41106469604f5b105c4

commit_message:
Run db-sync if nova packages are upgraded

This changes the db-sync logic to run if the api or common package is
upgraded.  Previously it would solely ensure that the api package was
installed before running db sync.  On ubuntu, if the common package is
upgraded then the api package will also be upgraded in the same
transaction, which means that no notify will be generated.

Lastly, this fixes the package collector to use the params names for the
packages, instead of hard coding nova-api

Change-Id: I4fcea354c5d663644592093ec617ee5b1c6f33e3

commit_message:
Fix RST tests

Now that I79da2cb55ae6b1849001fe05f96c4ed35351c356 is merged we need to
actually follow the template and use correct RST syntax. This patch
corrects some of our errors and modifies the tests to align with our
template.

Change-Id: Ic86a30fc7ce63a287578ee01c7fa11ce5f785577

commit_message:
Introduce command-dict and validator

Refactor `vm.utils._run_command_over_ssh' making it accept a dict to
specify command as either local script file, inline script or remote
script path. Both local and inline scripts require `interpreter' being
specified. Any of the above can be a list specifying e.g. environment
variables (for `interpreter') or command args.

Introduce `valid_command' validator that checks whether the specified
command dictionary is a valid one.

Change-Id: I3c495297251c87529b9adf1e769cfe277338f5fc
Implements: blueprint vm-workloads-framework

and checks cross connectivity.

The wheel that was generated was bad. The wheel was not in fact universal (it broke on Python 3). The wheel has been removed from PyPI.'}, {'account_id': 4190, 'date': '2015-06-08 17:40:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

@Ian, did you read the bug? The wheel was bad because setup.py was bad, pip 7 autogenerates wheels, so every single user everywhere will get bads wheels.'}, {'account_id': 12000, 'date': '2015-06-08 18:11:03.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: -Code-Review

The last I read it, Julian had removed the wheel which fixed glance's gate. The problem is more intricate than you (or others on that bug) present. It isn't simply the fact that pip auto-builds wheels now, it's that it also caches them.

If pip auto-built a wheel for 2.7 that was cached only for 2.7 and another for 3.x that was only cached for 3.x then this wouldn't be an issue. Auto-building the wheel on 3.x would not have this problem since `python setup.py bdist_wheel` is being run under Python 3. That makes that wheel broken for 2.7 but not for other installations on Python 3. Likewise, if pip auto-builds the wheel under 2.7, it breaks the installation for 3.x but not for other 2.7 installations. So it isn't a bad requirements issue, it's a problem with using old hacks for managing dependencies based on Python versioning. The requirements themselves are fine, it's generating a bad wheel that tries to install them on the wrong version of Python"}, {'account_id': 5263, 'date': '2015-06-08 18:30:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1

Looks from https://github.com/Julian/jsonschema/pull/231 like a new release is imminent but best to have this break documented in our reqs anyway.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-06-08 18:30:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: -Verified

commit_message:
Clean only floating-ip related connection states

Currently init_l3 deletes connection states related to ALL ips deleted
in init_l3 but it's required only when floating-ips are deleted[1].

This change deletes only connection states related to floating-ips
deleted in init_l3 ... it avoids to delete connection states in dhcp
agents and on router internal ports!

[1] look at change Ia9bd7ae243a0859dcb97e2fa939f7d16f9c2456c

Closes-Bug: #1452434
Related-Bug: #1334926
Change-Id: Icfcfc585df6fd41de1e1345fd731e4631a6950ce

commit_message:
Added more unit-tests to improve code coverage

Following files were too low on code coverage,
so the coverage has been enhanced with addition of more unit-tests.
- troveclient/client.py
- troveclient/v1/shell.py

The methodology to test shell.py has been motivated from the
one used by python-novaclient to test novaclient/v2/shell.py

Also, found an unmocked entry in test_secgroups.py,
which was causing intermittent failure while
writing the tests for shell.py.

Closes-Bug: #1455856
Change-Id: I6a148fb5caad6a83b6ac23411b6458f231064ead

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-06-04 18:53:31.000000000', 'message': "Add provider extension support

Adds support for the 'provider:network_type' field in network
creation. This is included in the 'provider' extension.

Other fields included in this extension (segmentation_id and physical_network)
are not supported.

The only value allowed for 'provider:network_type' is 'local'.

This means that the user is allowed to specify that a network with the
fields 'provider:network_type':'local' if he chooses. This information
is then given to the midonet backend so that the backend can treat
this network as a 'provider network', which is described in specs/provider_net.

Implements: specs/provider_net
Change-Id: I475388612a941b6511da1781bca2971270052abb
Fixes: MNP-73

commit_message:
Add provider extension support

Adds support for the 'provider:network_type' field in network
creation. This is included in the 'provider' extension.

Other fields included in this extension (segmentation_id and physical_network)
are not supported.

The only value allowed for 'provider:network_type' is 'local'.

This means that the user is allowed to specify that a network with the
fields 'provider:network_type':'local' if he chooses. This information
is then given to the midonet backend so that the backend can treat
this network as a 'provider network', which is described in specs/provider_net.

Co-Authored-By: Joe Mills <joe@midokura.com>

Implements: specs/provider_net
Change-Id: I475388612a941b6511da1781bca2971270052abb
Fixes: MNP-73

commit_message:
Add --insecure/-k option to cfn-signal

cfn-signal will not work when heat-cfn-api server is configured
for the https. This patch will provide a option to make a insecure
request to the cfn server.

Change-Id: I9dcd53b40a389811e292c331ff625a8b5af827b7
Closes-Bug: 1460007

anything other than the most conservative capacity and usage information
up to the scheduler

This commit:
  *  modifies the NetApp drivers to use the nfs_oversub_ratio as
     documented.
  *  uses direct API with filers to gather capacity information rather
     than stat and du commands
  *  brings our reporting of reserved percentage in line with the way
     the scheduler actually makes use of this statistic
  *  simplifies and cleans up the way we gather and report pool statistics

and is intended to be the basis for backported fixes.

     max_oversubscription_ratio

rather than the driver reporting "apparent" free space.

NFS driver is not intended as a substitute for introducing support
in our drivers for the newer approach to overprovisioning.  Rather,

commit_message:
Use nfs_oversub_ratio when reporting pool capacity

Currently NetApp NFS drivers do not make use of the nfs_oversub_ratio
configuration parameter to enable OpenStack administrators to report
anything other than the most conservative capacity and usage information
up to the scheduler

This commit:
  *  modifies the NetApp drivers to use the nfs_oversub_ratio as
     documented.
  *  uses direct API with filers to gather capacity information rather
     than stat and du commands
  *  brings our reporting of reserved percentage in line with the way
     the scheduler actually makes use of this statistic
  *  simplifies and cleans up the way we gather and report pool statistics

Note that this fix addresses an in-the-field bug report from juno
and is intended to be the basis for backported fixes.

In kilo, a more general approach to overprovisioning using
     max_oversubscription_ratio
was introduced via commit 3548a4bc9edbb26b248b5af5ecc2145f2c6f7481.
In this newer approach, the scheduler computes "virtual" free space
rather than the driver reporting "apparent" free space.

This fix to bring NetApp NFS drivers into conformity with the generic
NFS driver is not intended as a substitute for introducing support
in our drivers for the newer approach to overprovisioning.  Rather,
it is a bug-fix for an existing failure to honor the nfs_oversub_ratio.

DocImpact
Co-Authored-By: Dustin Schoenbrun <dustin.schoenbrun@netapp.com>
Closes-bug: 1449620
Change-Id: Ic7b606b88f063b9ed6df62fd1fb7248922496326
(cherry picked from commit e52f304313efc695f7dd89c222041bffd53c131a)

commit_message:
MongoDB user management commands

Spec for enabling various user management commands for MongoDB.
user-create, list, and delete,
root-enable and show,
and user-grant- and revoke-access  will be supported.

Change-Id: I71f7226cdd07446b2ca19f42f711544e93f288dd
Implements: blueprint mongodb-users

commit_message:
Refactoring heat deployer's multi-port checking code

The code which checks whether all the ports of the DU are active
was coupled with the code that ran the check for du_attempts
number of time. This coupling was incorrect. If the du_attempts
was less than the number of ports, we would have ended up not
checking all the ports.

This patch fixes this situation. We decouple the checking of the ports
from trying the check du_attempts times. We also maintain a list of
successful_ports so that in each du_attempt we only check those ports
which have not yet been successfully reachable.

Change-Id: Ib82e5547d9ab2184df3b3e3800301925d5682284

commit_message:
Add launchpad tag used by "Report a bug"

"Report a bug" automatically populates bugs on launchpad with
information about the manual. This additional config setting
will allow "Report a bug" to automatically tag the bug with the
respective manual.

Change-Id: Iba782b715a3c730df1c199c7f73fbba1744aa37e

commit_message:
Enable congress and tempest in devstack in congress-dsvm-api test

A number of fixes:
- Congress was not being installed
- the tempest tests were disabled
- the enabled services were not explicitly defined
- python-congressclient was not being pulled from git
- tempest tests were not being copied into Tempest

Change-Id: If1aecf6f3383350157811cad154a8cb22107f95a

commit_message:
Support for the new Devstack plugin model in Rally

Currently Rally uses old extras.d method for integration with
Devstack. This change adds support of the new Devstack plugin
approach [1] in CI jobs to be able to implement it in Rally.

[1] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/devstack/plugins.html

Change-Id: I4dc55274d9b1e720fc122e07c487699e589c6f5a

these are hardware dependent tests that are based on tempest scenario test. e.g. these test launch VMs and validate that the numa topology, numa based pci scheduling, cpu pinning and hugepage allocation are configured correctly. due to their hardware dependency they cannot be run in VMs or up streamed to tempest.

this is testing code that is part of nova that cannot be tested in the gate due to its hardware dependency.
these test have no dependency on any third party additions to nova and only test the in tree code.

we are creating this repo as a result of a direct request form the nova core team before commenting on nova patchsets.'}, {'account_id': 1, 'date': '2015-06-05 22:20:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 6547, 'date': '2015-06-08 19:35:32.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-06-08 19:35:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: -Verified

commit_message:
Add intel-nfv-ci-tests repo to stackforge

This patch introduces a new repo to store the testcases run in
the intel nfv ci. This ci will validate numa placement, cpu pinning
and hugepage memory allocation on physical hardware.

Change-Id: I39faeead4979f9c0053dea953dcfa5181f49c90b

commit_message:
Don't support deprecated drivers' vendor_passthru

In Kilo, a common mechanism was added that all drivers use for exposing
their vendor methods. Drivers' own implementations of vendor_passthru()
method was deprecated, and backwards compatibility was maintained for any
out-of-tree drivers that still implemented their own version of the
vendor_passthru() method.

This change removes support for that backwards compatibility.

Change-Id: I5e134e42449f2bbeefee1f9cb1712f59fa7a2b9f

commit_message:
Fixing data processing operations for alternate webroots

No longer doing a urlresolver.resolve on the path for any
requests.  Instead, we are now using query style params
which is the way the rest of the sahara dashboard does
things.

Change-Id: Iad413bdf618a4f5374df1fd40793c0b609b17d99
Closes-Bug: #1450535

commit_message:
Make second level of Rabbit OCF monitor only at slaves

W/o this fix, monitor check level 30 is not always
added into the CIB for RabbitMQ pacemaker resource.

The w/a is to define second monitor only for slaves.

Closes-bug: #1462899

Change-Id: I678b4af19e846a2a7f6c4ce829a1a8b5a4391876
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

[{'created': '2015-05-27 00:14:56.000000000', 'message': 'Install zlib1g-dev for puppet beaker jobs

The latest version of beaker-rspec depends on Nokogiri 1.6.x. We are
currently pinning beaker-rspec to 2.2.x which brings in Nokogiri 1.5.x.
Nokogiri 1.6.x has libxml2-dev and libxslt-dev vendored within the gem,
so once we unpin beaker-rspec we will no longer need to install those
packages.  However, on Debian/Ubuntu we still need to install the
header libraries which come in the zlib1g-dev package and which do not
seem to be included in libxml2-dev or libxslt-dev. If we do not, then
attempting to use the latest version of beaker-rspec results in gem
installation errors[1]. This patch adds the new package, zlib1g-dev, so
that both Nokogiri 1.5 and 1.6 will work, and therefore beaker-rspec
2.2 and latest will work. See the troubleshooting documentation[2] for
more information.

[1] http://logs.openstack.org/61/185161/1/check/gate-puppet-nova-puppet-beaker-rspec-dsvm-trusty/2152ed2/console.html.gz#_2015-05-22_21_53_47_219
[2] http://www.nokogiri.org/tutorials/installing_nokogiri.html#ubuntu___debian

Change-Id: Iefdf96325e11b470e864d5386a3eab0eb655c960
'}]
commit_message:
Install zlib1g-dev for puppet beaker jobs

The latest version of beaker-rspec depends on Nokogiri 1.6.x. We are
currently pinning beaker-rspec to 2.2.x which brings in Nokogiri 1.5.x.
Nokogiri 1.6.x has libxml2-dev and libxslt-dev vendored within the gem,
so once we unpin beaker-rspec we will no longer need to install those
packages.  However, on Debian/Ubuntu we still need to install the
header libraries which come in the zlib1g-dev package and which do not
seem to be included in libxml2-dev or libxslt-dev. If we do not, then
attempting to use the latest version of beaker-rspec results in gem
installation errors[1]. This patch adds the new package, zlib1g-dev, so
that both Nokogiri 1.5 and 1.6 will work, and therefore beaker-rspec
2.2 and latest will work. See the troubleshooting documentation[2] for
more information.

[1] http://logs.openstack.org/61/185161/1/check/gate-puppet-nova-puppet-beaker-rspec-dsvm-trusty/2152ed2/console.html.gz#_2015-05-22_21_53_47_219
[2] http://www.nokogiri.org/tutorials/installing_nokogiri.html#ubuntu___debian

Change-Id: Iefdf96325e11b470e864d5386a3eab0eb655c960

commit_message:
Refactor verify_create in proxy tests

This is the first of several changes to cleanup the proxy tests and
their duplicated verification mocks.

Note: this is slightly changed for the test_messages_create and
test_messages_claim tests in TestMessageProxy. They aren't using the
BaseProxy methods so they need to be implemented slightly differently.
It's not entirely clear how they were actually working before because it
was mocking out a method the call doesn't go through.

Change-Id: I16e28b3126a474fd14a9fdde433620009a83bf29

commit_message:
Document the IPv6 subnet attributes

This introduces the possible settings for ipv6_ra_mode and
ipv6_address_mode. This table differs in many ways from the original
table[1], but contains clarifications that might be ported back over to
neutron-specs.

For instance, the combinations of ipv6_address_mode set with
ipv6_ra_mode unset, where the Neutron ML2 plugin has not implemented
these features have been specificed as "Not Implemented."

The only behavior for when ipv6_address_mode is set and ipv6_ra_mode is
set to "slaac" that has been defined, is spcified by the following
spec[2].

[1]: http://specs.openstack.org/openstack/neutron-specs/specs/juno/ipv6-radvd-ra.html

[2]: http://specs.openstack.org/openstack/neutron-specs/specs/juno/ipv6-provider-nets-slaac.html

Change-Id: Ie4c56cc502baa389a5ac5f654ee3f4fee5f4a041
Related-Bug: #1293897

[{'created': '2015-06-02 19:29:57.000000000', 'message': "Check for existing mapping of inst disk to mgmt

An attempt to add an already-exist mapping will result in a 500 error
from PowerVM.  As written, the disk driver's
connect_instance_disk_to_mgmt routine will swallow this error, move on
to the next VIOS, and try to add the mapping there.  If that VIOS also
already has the mapping, we run out of VIOSes and the entire method
fails.  If it doesn't, we add the (same) mapping there as well,
resulting in two equivalent mappings.

The caller of connect_instance_disk_to_mgmt simply expects as a
postcondition that an appropriate mapping (preferably just one) exists.
This change set modifies the method to check whether the VIOS it is
inspecting already has an appropriate mapping; and if so, it shorts out
successfully.

Change-Id: If928dafb527a8e828c85dfcf13f5a7228c567fe5

commit_message:
Optimizations for SCSI mappings

Recent pypowervm changes in the scsi_mapper task library have enabled
specifying an already-retrieved VIOS wrapper instead of a VIOS UUID
(which is subsequently used to retrieve the VIOS wrapper).  Herein we
take advantage of those changes to minimize the number of expensive
PowerVM REST API calls.

Change-Id: If928dafb527a8e828c85dfcf13f5a7228c567fe5

commit_message:
Update devstack to handle Trove/Neutron setups

Default Trove configuration (for task manager and service) don't
reflect the settings required for Neutron. Trove requires a
configuration that can only be done after neutron is up. This
introduces a new function called just before starting trove services.

Change-Id: I197ec2d3975f7b551590cf1f6c7d2cb42d479e25
Closes-Bug: #1435612

commit_message:
Add volume drivers for Infortrend Storage

Infortrend implement ISCSI and FC volume drivers for
EonStor DS product.
It manages storage by Infortrend CLI tool.

common_cli.py implements the basic Cinder Driver API.
infortrend_fc_cli.py and infortrend_iscsi_cli.py use them to
provide FC and iSCSI specific support.

Support features:
- Volume Create/Delete
- Volume Attach/Detach
- Snapshot Create/Delete
- Create Volume from Snapshot
- Get Volume Stats
- Copy Image to Volume
- Copy Volume to Image
- Clone Volume
- Extend Volume

Change-Id: I753f88072c9c073bcb44d203b70cd79ce1aac186
Implements: blueprint infortrend-iscsi-fc-volume-driver

commit_message:
Init UUIDCache in test_instance_exists

Depending on the order in which tox runs tests,
nova-powervm.tests.virt.powervm.test_vm.TestVM.test_instance_exists can
fail *intermittently* with:

Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/home/jenkins/workspace/gate-nova-powervm-python27/.tox/py27/
local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/mock.py", line 1201, in patched
    return func(*args, **keywargs)
  File "nova_powervm/tests/virt/powervm/test_vm.py", line 289, in
test_instance_exists
    self.assertTrue(vm.instance_exists(*mock_parms))
  File "nova_powervm/virt/powervm/vm.py", line 229, in instance_exists
    uuid = cache.lookup(instance.name, fetch=False)
AttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'lookup'

...because UUIDCache needs to be initialized (by calling its
constructor) before it is used.

The reliable way to reproduce the problem is to run this test case by
itself, e.g.

tox -e py27 -- nova-powervm.tests.virt.powervm.test_vm.TestVM.test_inst
ance_exists

Change-Id: I6584a8e390d0cc8d8bfe0b7de476d4c37de11a64

commit_message:
Remove unused find_attribute_or_element()

find_attribute_or_element() is not used since the first commit
(c53d8e343e50d4cf7ea9a6a81258848c2d893bfb), then this patch removes
the method.

commit_message:
Build jessie ramdisk

Instructs DIB to use jessie instead of wheezy for the appliance
VM base.  This'll speed up boot time thanks to systemd.

Change-Id: Ie6a19c8c5029f55da5fb912211117fe9c7476779
Depends-On: Id4b997848edee21bdcfa3d9defedc69598eccfad

commit_message:
Preserve logs in logs/ folder

Add retention of logs from a test run in a delineated folder
so OpenStack CI can be configured to store the logs after a
completed test.

Change-Id: I8d686918649a69b8aab9e3c5d7faf3a79a42a4e8
Partial-Bug: 1459803

commit_message:
Flavor tests - use a digest cycle to test watches

This refactors the flavor test patch to use the digest cycle to
test watches. This fixes a dependency the prior version of the
tests had on the order of the code under test.

Change-Id: Idf2e5cf93d911b498c899dd3fa42821511755455

commit_message:
[Launch Instance Fix] Add Flavor Step Unit Tests

- flavor.js code coverage up to 80%

This patch adds unit tests for the flavor step.  These tests are focused
around the controller and its related components (no selenium tests or view
tests).

Co-Authored-By: Mike Hagedorn <mike.hagedorn@hp.com>

Change-Id: Ia9cca258eacc36ac279cf6d21ffa2197f58d9294
Partial-Bug: 1435869

(1 comment)

Question inline for other reviewers to consider.  If it is not something we see as a concern then I'll put a +2."}, {'account_id': 14070, 'date': '2015-06-03 12:46:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

I agree, that makes me a bit uncomfortable as well.

The consuming code is using the UUID, short ID, and name.  I really didn't want to pass all three of those things down separately.

One alternative to consider - at one point in my development I was loading the management partition wrapper in the *disk* driver (rather than the main driver).  This doesn't really change the fact of keeping the whole wrapper around while it might be changing, but it avoids passing it in via the connection dict."}, {'account_id': 8190, 'date': '2015-06-04 00:04:32.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Do we really think anything but the name and uuid is going to be passed around?

If not...I really would prefer we do pass them down independently.

Only other possible parameters I could see might be the lpar ID (not UUID).  But I personally would rather play it safe than sorry...'}, {'account_id': 14070, 'date': '2015-06-04 14:06:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

We use the name (for log messages), the UUID (to add mappings), and the short ID (to remove mappings).

So: do you want me to pass those three items individually?'}, {'account_id': 8190, 'date': '2015-06-04 16:30:59.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

That's where I'm leaning.  I just keep convincing myself the alternative is too dangerous.

A third option is to make a small class with just those elements (as we've had the same need for VIOS LPARs in the past)...but I was thinking that might be too heavy weight at this time."}, {'account_id': 14070, 'date': '2015-06-04 16:35:37.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

I considered a miniature sparse wrapper-esque class, but thought that would be even more confusing, since it would look and behave just like an LPAR EntryWrapper with respect to those three values.

I'm looking at pypowervm changes that might eliminate the need for the short ID.  And the log messages could use the UUID instead of the name - along with 'management partition' in the log message, that should be sufficient to identify it.  Then we would only need the UUID passed around at driver init.  Stay tuned."}, {'account_id': 14070, 'date': '2015-06-04 21:34:11.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-06-04 22:28:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified-1

commit_message:
Get the management partition at driver init

The pypowervm LPAR wrapper for the management partition is used for its
UUID, which is expected not to change.  It therefore makes sense to load
up this UUID once, at driver init time.

This change set also refactors/optimizes a few other lookups into their
highest common base class.

Change-Id: Id53fdf029c17f8296a7a9088548e0351a7901924

commit_message:
Fix functional tests and tox 2.0 errors

With the recent update to tox 2.0.x, environment variables such as
OS_AUTH_URL are not passed by default, resulting in tests errors
mentionning Keystone authentication failures.

This patch reads credentials from the 'functional_creds.conf' config
file, like it is done in novaclient, glanceclient, manilaclient and
soon in cinderclient.

Reading credentials the old way (the environment) is still possible.

Change-Id: Ief0f050044ecd90a14bbaf044e2b93ade0a6173f
Closes-Bug: #1455102

commit_message:
Checkout devstack-gate master in periodic jobs

Periodic jobs don't have branch or ref set, so provide defaults
for those for the devstack-checkout (which now uses zuul-cloner
and therefore requires them).

Change-Id: I373b30de3e694ffe30b6b3819aaff6823777974e

commit_message:
Fix for listing role assignments by project admin

Project admin fails to list role assignments for his project with
Project Scoped Token.
The issue is project admin in default policy file
(policy.v3cloudsample.json) does not have access to get details
of his project. Due to this, keystone assumes that the project
does not exist, and tries to get the project listing which again
fails.
This change updates the default policy file to let project
administrators to retrieve their own project details.

Change-Id: I4f257c3b955a10ff492cd909791a3c4469bd139c
Closes-Bug: 1418702

commit_message:
Bring Redhat support to acceptance tests

OpenStack Infra has jobs to run this on both Ubuntu Trusty and
OS7.

* Add minitest to Gemfile (dependency to run beaker on centos - see
  http://projects.theforeman.org/issues/2650 for details)
* separate nodepool files to have trusty & centos7 support in OS
* infra
* spec: add case for repo configuration and support
  RH systems.
* rabbitmq: install module from source
* apt: pin the module
* configure device_driver for LBaaS (update in Kilo)

Change-Id: If6c724243ba2e4932b1121b7b7f148d8b5a3f187
Closes-bug: #1444736

commit_message:
Set places to 0 in self.assertAlmostEqual()

We are checking time of thread run in test_impl_rabbit.py and sometimes
it can be a bit longer, because of server load.

Set places=0 instead of 1 to make tests less restrictive.

Change-Id: I2ef6f1474047e1da64402e93696cb73b4d3318e8

commit_message:
Reduce `magic` conf attribute usage

Connection class contains `magic` attribute conf, which contains (or at
least should contain) all config options. Set these config options as
class attributes to make the code more clear

commit_message:
Bring Redhat support to acceptance tests

OpenStack Infra has jobs to run this on both Ubuntu Trusty and
OS7.

* Add minitest to Gemfile (dependency to run beaker on centos - see
  http://projects.theforeman.org/issues/2650 for details)
* separate nodepool files to have trusty & centos7 support in OS
  infra
* install openstack_extras module
* install EPEL on RH systems

Change-Id: Ib0e14a8e866ffafc2fb47bb72b4ee40a7f4d0230
Closes-bug: #1444736

commit_message:
Update GA tracking code

The OpenStack foundation maintains a Google Analytics
account for tracking access. The stats from this
account will be shared regularly with docaedo,
who will then share these stats with the appropriate
MLs (similar to how this has been handled by the
OpenStack docs team).

This commit updates the tracking code so visits to
the App Catalog are properly tracked by using a new
sub-code for GA and also sending anchor tags along
with the clicks.

Closes-Bug: 1461167

Change-Id: Ie87f6da290718e8b8dcc72f65f588161f923c03d

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. The more you
    participate in the community the more rewarding it is for you. You may also
    notice that the more you get to know people and get to be known, the faster
    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others
    and become known by doing code reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a
    great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

commit_message:
Check for NotFound exception in setUp() function

test_resize_server_confirm_from_stopped test works fine when executed
alone but during a group execution it tries to delete the same instance
multiple times.

setUp() function is modified so that it catches NotFound exception and
create a new server instead of rebuilding (=deleting and creating) the
previous one.

Change-Id: Ie411268e37e4348a2434b473cd84e151a0a18c09
Closes-Bug: #1459516

Fix fail test_iscsi_volume

In _volume_clean_up method to get volume used volumes_client
with get_volume while show_volume should be used instead

Closes-bug: #1451759

commit_message:
Set default event status to completed

Change I9a22e53ca872235e723798d8ce3cb146d88568ab altered the
processing order of the events which broke logic to populate
the event status as 'completed' by default. This broke the
network changed events from Neutron.

This change modifies the logic to preserve the default 'completed'
behavior and adjusts a unit tests to prevent a regression.

Closes-Bug: #1462851
Change-Id: I3f4d10740138f65d704d6f8fa4db06d3d0ed64cf

commit_message:
Config & deployments to update overcloud packages

This change adds config and deployment resources to trigger package
updates on nodes. The deployments are triggered by doing a stack-update
and setting one of the parameters to a unique value.

The intent is that rolling update will be controlled by setting
breakpoints on all of the UpdateDeployment resources inside the
role resource groups.

Change-Id: I56bbf944ecd6cbdbf116021b8a53f9f9111c134f

commit_message:
Remove floating_ip_source

Now that we can reliably determine the network service provider for all
the supported clouds, we can remove floating_ip_source as it would be
only used to determine if floating IPs are available.

To check if floating IPs are available, we can just query the extension
list of Nova or Neutron.

Change-Id: I266c11085e5ee739aa58e150219f84ed9d2c1575

commit_message:
Allow overriding the network service provider

The purpose of this patch is to make has_service() work again in the
shade library.

The catalog of some clouds lies: it say it supports a sevice (e.g.
neutron) but that service is not reachable. Rax is the most notable
example.

With this patch we add 'network_provider', a new attribute, without
default value. Currently, the only vendor that needs this attribute
is Rax.

Given this new attribute, we don't need to specify the
floating_ip_source anymore because we can determine if floating IPs are
supported just looking at the os-floating-ip nova extension.
We can do the same for secgroups (security-group extension of Neutron
or SecurityGroups extension of Nova), but removing these attributes
could break backward compatibility and it would be better handled in
separate patches.

Change-Id: I6eec5e58c72ec2cb80f926fca40ffef0d07df93b

pypowervm.tasks.scsi_mapper return the VIOS EntryWrapper for the Virtual

<ihrachyshka> dims__, while versionutils module allows us to report just those that we explicitly request
<ihrachyshka> comments?

<dims__> ihrachyshka: then i'd be ok for you to continue with that but the one from oslo.log
<ihrachyshka> we wanted to extend versionutils to support keyword deprecation, but were asked to use debtcollector.
<ihrachyshka> so we looked into it and don't get how to enable warnings without bloating logs with irrelevant stuff
<dims__> let's involve dhellmann and harlowja in this discussion as it is important.
<dims__> ihrachyshka: point me to the review please?
<ihrachyshka> dims__, neutron review that raised the need of keyword deprecation: https://review.openstack.org/175238

commit_message:
Introduce @deprecated_parameter decorator

It can be used to deprecate specific arguments for a callable, while
leaving callable intact in terms of deprecation.

Unit tests for @deprecated are generalized, and those applicable for
@deprecated_parameter are moved into a common mixin class to reuse for
both deprecation classes.

For reference, the particular need for such a decorator arised in one of
neutron reviews: I8a5c02712a0b43f3e36a4f14620ebbd73fbfb03f

Change-Id: If396f8ea7d6d31e67ae7f9fb223b21982f97ce7a
Closes-Bug: #1461043

commit_message:
Update ipset members when corresponding sg member is empty

if a security group has a rule with 'remote-group-id', the ports
in this security group should update its relevant ipset member
when the remote-group members is empty.

Change-Id: I980ebfd8f6537f803d9d5cbf21ca33f727fea3b3
Closes-bug: #1458786

commit_message:
Make sure sysrq functions are enabled in reboot.sh

This commit echoes '1' to >/proc/sys/kernel/sysrq to
make sure that sysrq functions are enabled before
invoking them.

Change-Id: I88697efbc1bd0dec5ed4cbcd8d89b0b5d0734bdd

commit_message:
Remove WritableLogger wrapper

After new release of oslo.log (1.2.0), we got messages about deprecation
of WritableLogger. We need to remove that.

Change-Id: I5627f2f7524b1a08f3179ee4bf85eabfea14d7a9

Closes-bug: 1461057

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-06-02 21:05:07.000000000', 'message': 'Disable neutron DEBUG logs

We are retrieving ALL neutron objects to check quotas. This could
lead to logs flooding.

Ideally quotas usage check should be done on neutron side, but it
looks there is no way to do that. Horizon retrieves all neutron
objects too.

So, just disabling DEBUG for neutron client.

Change-Id: Ic5f28c76e5d1a628e0323efa8fe3980577ca37a5
Closes-Bug: #1459794
'}]
commit_message:
Disable neutron DEBUG logs

We are retrieving ALL neutron objects to check quotas. This could
lead to logs flooding.

Ideally quotas usage check should be done on neutron side, but it
looks there is no way to do that. Horizon retrieves all neutron
objects too.

So, just disabling DEBUG for neutron client.

Change-Id: Ic5f28c76e5d1a628e0323efa8fe3980577ca37a5
Closes-Bug: #1459794

commit_message:
Add "null" for fields in cluster and node group template JSON schemas

* Change 'type' for optional fields to list including 'null'

* Allow the default template tool to use "None" to
unset fields with replacement values when no replacement has been
specified.

* Fix cluster template update code to check for explicit setting of
the 'node_groups' field in a cluster template update

Partial-Bug: #1438077
Closes-Bug: #1439839

Change-Id: Ia180867c8e3ffb502da40f169a49dd3a54c23072

commit_message:
Enable NetApp Backends in Cinder

Enables support for configuring Cinder with a NetApp backend.
This change adds all relevant parameters for:
 - Clustered Data ONTAP (NFS, iSCSI, FC)
 - Data ONTAP 7-Mode (NFS, iSCSI, FC)
 - E-Series (iSCSI)

Change-Id: If6c6e511ef2d26c4794e3b37c61e5318485ff4db

commit_message:
Fix assertRaisesRegexp deprecation warnings in UT

This commit changes assertRaisesRegexp occurrences to
assertRaisesRegex to fix deprecation warnings.

Change-Id: I22fb6224057716f734a8ac69da72ccdb9b464289
Closes-Bug: 1461171

commit_message:
Setup logging in the appliance

The appliance currently tries to log to /tmp/gunicorn.log, but thats
misconfigured.  This sets gunicorn up to log to /var/log/akanda/ for
both access and error logs and installs and configures logrotate for
those files.

Change-Id: Ie75f305860a0c5204ec8fe5b1af0de03826aa880

commit_message:
Add value format for list command

The value format for the show command is very handy for shell
scripting and a value format for the list command would be just
as handy.  It will allow command substitution and piping like:

    os container list --format value | grep tmp | while read NAME
    do
      os container delete $NAME
    done

Change-Id: If9784c27d689073e9145b2cb8077ac604025a4c3

DATADIR-TMPDIR-ASYNCDIR

Remove duplicated definitions of DATADIR, TMPDIR, ASYNCDIR

Also treated QUARENTINED
And reorginized all dirs in a central dictionary

commit_message:
Use install_default_policy

Recent versions of oslo-incubator/policy expects to find a
`policy.d` dir inside $PROJECT_CONF_DIR. Otherwise it would
log the message  "Can not find policy directory: policy.d".

This modifies install_default_policy to ensure the directory is
created and adds a note about why.  The projects are converted to use
this function rather than copy by hand.  Some minor changes are
required to handle layout differences between projects.

Change-Id: I335a661d307a330e8b59883ef60c787c6590eb42

oslo.config makes attempts to autodiscover configuration files using
find_config_files() helper. If e.g. /etc/neutron/neutron.conf exists,
and is not readable, the following test failure can be experienced:

oslo_config.cfg.ConfigFilesPermissionDeniedError: Failed to open some
config files: /etc/neutron/neutron.conf

Unit tests must not rely on any external state of the system and run
successfully no matter whether neutron is actually installed on the
system, or not.

commit_message:
tests: don't allow oslo.config to autodiscover config files

oslo.config makes attempts to autodiscover configuration files using
find_config_files() helper. If e.g. /etc/neutron/neutron.conf exists,
and is not readable, the following test failure can be experienced:

oslo_config.cfg.ConfigFilesPermissionDeniedError: Failed to open some
config files: /etc/neutron/neutron.conf

Unit tests must not rely on any external state of the system and run
successfully no matter whether neutron is actually installed on the
system, or not.

Closes-Bug: #1442543
Change-Id: Ic90d8c40b2072fdda152703b84081719936b5f4e

commit_message:
Include NetApp Cinder Dependencies in Images

The NetApp drivers for Cinder will need to use these protocols:
 - iSCSI (iscsi-initiator-utils)
 - NFS (nfs-utils)
 - Fibre Channel (no packages needed)

Change-Id: I78edde345689333091b8d0d39e1436fa92db8c5a

Modify ping floating ip command

commit_message:
Allow oslo rabbit heartbeat configuration

In order to allow components to better handle and respond to mq failures,
oslo has some heartbeat options that are useful.

Change-Id: I75b2b5e140095bdc828df6af13159170aa08839c

commit_message:
Improve disk-unit angular filters

Bug 1447814: The Bytes filter should go up to petabyte values.  (The
python equivelents do, so don't lose feature parity.)

Refactor of the gb and mb filters.
Added pb, tb, and kb filters.
bytes filter now accepts specific label.

commit_message:
Add missing hadoop version check for CDH 5.4

If you specify 5.4 version for Cloudera, now it will crash
with error 'unknown version'

Change-Id: I06ee3de903dba88673114859a3e69aa4396093d1

commit_message:
Allow relative names in record-create

Currently record-create requires absolute names. This change allows to
provide relative (to the domain) names with the new option --relative.

Change-Id: I78258ea734a4105fae8f9f3ef30fe86e018b5388
Closes-Bug: #1444452

Modify ping floating ip command

to use it with count number to prevent it from hanging

commit_message:
Allow for building non-wheezy releases

This makes the kernel update task only happen on wheezy and removes
the default release stuff from bird (the newer backports version should be
installed without pinning to that repo)

Change-Id: Id4b997848edee21bdcfa3d9defedc69598eccfad

commit_message:
Bump gunicorn worker timeout to 60

The default 30s worker timeout for gunicorn is not sufficient for
some slower environments, as the metadata service takes a while to
restart.  This bumps it to 60s to ensure we dont fail config updates
on worker timeouts.

Change-Id: If27329b58d97e6aef687a069615dbda763dba8c1
Closes-bug: #1462100

commit_message:
Make router_instance_flavor a StrOpt

Nova supports non-int flavor IDs (ie, UUIDs). Update the config and make
this setting a string, not int.

Change-Id: I0c6deb213619fae6281efb2a063da27c5258ab7a

commit_message:
devstack: Create a custom nova flavor for the appliance

m1.small is overkill for our purposes, but a micro is too small for our
image.  This creates a flavor with bigger disk support but less memory.

Change-Id: I1f4072e864f956df10511ec75b4a043ef7f4d838

commit_message:
Pass response body down into RestClientExceptions

This commit adds support to RestClientException objects to store the
response body as a local attr. Additionally it modifies all the uses
of the subclassed RestClientExceptions in the base rest client to
store the response body on each error type.

This is done in order to check the content in some occasion that
additional error details are coming back from a service in the body.
It will be useful to have the resp_body passed into the exception so
that it can be used in additional checks.

commit_message:
Adding user_id handling to keypair create api call

Allowing the administrator to be able to create new
keypairs on behalf of their users

Related to blueprint admin-query-any-keypair

Change-Id: Iab7fdf5e50cce7c5682f697a67b08d73bf7fd491

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

commit_message:
Attempt to make pylint output more useful

Fixed incorrectly reported location of duplicate code.
Some new code checks added:
W0612(unused-variable): Unused variable 'e'
W0613(unused-argument): Unused argument 'x'
C1001(old-style-class): Old-style class defined

Change-Id: I7e20d9347c672f1df6fc3c270fc966f0a570ef6a

commit_message:
New "logical architecture" page in cloud admin guide

The text on this page seems to be copied directly from a
developer guide and is largely irrelevant for admins.
Text must be rewritten, and the diagram, which depicts
the situation at Havana time, must be redrawn.

Change-Id: I8f0a9538661292619bd8375ae03d20fe3cee2b5e
Closes-Bug: #1431079

commit_message:
Intern-based unit tests

This commit adds unit-tests runner for UI and 1 test suite for
the expression parser. It also makes --webui flag for run_tests.sh
run all the UI tests: lint checks, unit tests, functional tests.

Change-Id: I6176dc01cdd6d2bcf7a99185e92cc498c7b2b899
